    Announcement: 'Perjantaikuulutukset! Friday…'

    Tiina Lampen
    Created 16 Sept 2023 16 Sept 2023
    Perjantaikuulutukset! Friday Announcements!
    So sorry for the late Friday announcements! My computer was not working properly yesterday and I couldn’t post this earlier.

    Ensi viikolla…
    maanantai:DVV; Tiina
    tiistai: Luonto, Tiina
    keskiviikko: Testit,Tiina
    torstai: Viimeinen oppitunti, Tiina

    Spoken skills to the MAX kello 12:30
    keskiviikko: Shoppailu, Netta

    20.9.Testit
    9:00-10:00 Kirjoittaminen
    10:30-11:30 Kuunteleminen
    12:00-13:00 Lukeminen

    Kaikki tehtävät täytyy olla tehtynä torstaina 21.9. kello 8:00! That is an actual, absolutely final deadline. If you wish to pass the training, all of your Mod 6 and 7 assignments need to be done.

    Kurssi loppuu!
    We will have our final lesson after the tests on Thursday. I will give you some tips on how to continue studying and you can ask me questions about Finnish or Finland if you want.

    I am gonna grade your finals right away on Wednesday.  Mä lähetän tulokset heti, kun tiedän. I am sure that there will be some results I can't give out without consulting Netta and/or Barona, but if this is the situation with your scoring, I'll let you know about that too. Basically possibilities are:
    1. Yay, you passed!
    2. Sorry, you did not pass, Moduuli 7 again with Saukot.
    3. Grading is still pending, I'll get back to you ASAP next week.
    4. You did not pass and have been transferred a couple times before, need to check with Barona, I'll get back to you ASAP.

    I will also you give some personal feedback despite the result or the situation.

    Hyvää viikonloppua! Nähdään ensi viikolla!

    Announcement: 'Perjantaikuulutukset! Friday…'

    Tiina Lampen
    Created 8 Sept 2023 8 Sept 2023
    Perjantaikuulutukset! Friday Announcements!

    Ensi viikolla…
    maanantai:Työvuorossa 1, Tiina
    tiistai: Työvuorossa 2, Tiina
    keskiviikko: Työvuorossa 3, Netta

    torstai: Puhetestin harjoitus, Tiina
    Olisi tosi hyvä, jos kaikki pääsevät paikalle. Käytämme samanlaista materiaalia kuin perjantain testissä (check more on that below). Aihe on Ongelmatilanteita töissä .

    Spoken skills to the MAX kello 12:30
    keskiviikko: Asuminen, Tiina

    Perjantaina on puhetesti! Katso sun aika taulukosta.

    Puhetesti
    Last time you had a bunch of questions to answer together. Now you will have a couple of questions, maybe a statement and some key words and then you will talk about the given topic. I'll show example material on Thursday. Otherwise the system is the same as before: a couple of minutes to prepare yourself and then talk, given material will be visible to you for the whole time. (The example of what the test material looks like is posted here, Puhetestin ja treenin esimerkki, we are not going to use that material for anything, it is just an example.)

    Possible topics of the test are:
    1. Ikääntyneen henkinen ja fyysinen aktiivisuus
    2. Ikääntyneen haasteet ja toimintakunto
    3. Ikääntyneen potilaan yleiset sairaudet ja niiden hoito
    4. Ikäystävällinen koti

    When the test starts you will be given one topic and some material for that. The topics might look complicated at the first glance, but we have been practicing all of those.

    20.9. Muut testit
    9:00-10:00 Kirjoittaminen
    10:30-11:30 Kuunteleminen
    12:00-13:00 Lukeminen

    Kaikki tehtävät täytyy olla tehtynä torstaina 21.9. kello 8:00! That is an actual, absolutely final deadline. If you wish to pass the training, all of your Mod 6 and 7 assignments need to be done. The assignments I posted today are your last independant assignments. There will be 3 more assignments about lessons, so the final assignment will be number 112.

    Hyvää viikonloppua! Nähdään ensi viikolla!

    Ensi viikolla…
    maanantai: Oikeudet ja velvollisuudet, Netta

    tiistai: Toivelaulut, Tiina
    You guys get to decide what we study on this lesson! Please, send me a message and let me know, what you would like to learn. We can review some old materials or study something new you are curious about. It can be grammar or anything about Finnish or Finland. Let me know, what you want to do.

    keskiviikko: -malla/-matta, Netta
    torstai: Kela, Netta

    Spoken skills to the MAX kello 12:30
    keskiviikko: Ruoka, Netta

    Moduulin 7 testit
    15.9. Puhetestit
    There won’t be a sign up sheet this time. I will be pairing you guys and give you a time slot. I am not doing this to be mean, but I want to have balanced pairs for the final test. I will listen to your wishes, so if you want to do the test with a specific person, let me know. Also let me know about any time restrictions you might have on 15th.

    Harjoituksen aihe on sää ja luonto. You'll get the material in the class, but you can already prepare yourself by revising vocabulary for the topic.

    perjantai: Puhetestit! Tarkista sun aika!
    Check the PDF for further instructions and themes of the spoken skills test.

    Some thoughts about spoken skills tests...

    Preparing for a spoken skills test is preparing for life after it. I mean if you just focus on the test and passing that, it won't do you any good.

    More is more. Try to answer more than one short sentence. Ask extra questions from your mates, if you can. Speaking does not require perfect grammar, so just let go of the thought that you have to be perfect. If you have your verbs conjugated and like location cases more or less in order, you'll be understood. This of course changes when you go and do the higher levels, I am mainly talking about beg-level tests, which this one is!

    You don't have time to write sentences in real life. Writing sentences and learning them by heart gets you so far, of course. That's why we do it. But at some point you will understand that there is a huge difference between spoken and written language. With speaking you just have to trust your gut and jump to the deep end. Speak!

    Listen! In life (and in spoken test) it is utterly frustrating when people don't listen to each other. That too is a skill. Part of the spoken test is also understanding one another and discussing a given topic. React, agree, disagree! You don't have to repeat what the other person says, if you agree, just tell them that you agree.
    Admit if you don't understand, ask to repeat or explain. Learn to explain! In the test you can say that you don't understand or know something. It is okay to ask, to skip, to pass or to be vague (or to lie...)

    Move forward! Many spoken tests fall for stubbornness. You have decided to talk about something even though you don't understand or know how. Just admit your defeat and take the next question or topic or something.

    We know you know how to read. You have limited time, so don't use that time to read the material out loud. Of course sometimes someone has to ask the question or read the statement, but not always, you can just let the conversation take you to the next part even without stating the question or referring to material, if not specifically asked.

    Announcement: 'Puhetesti Tänään on puhetestipäivä,…'

    Tiina Lampen
    Created 12 May 2023 12 May 2023 (Edited 12 May 2023)
    Puhetesti
    Tänään on puhetestipäivä, hurraa!
    It is spoken skills test day, hooray!

    I know that you might be feeling anxious and stressed, but try to breathe and calm down. This is not super difficult or scary, we have been practicing for this. It is just me, Netta and some old spoken skills questions.

    Important things to remember are as follows:

    Try to find as quiet, calm and comfortable a place as you can for the test. All extra noise disturbs your focus as well as your group mate's. Closets and bathrooms have been very popular places in the past.

    You need to have your microphone and camera on during the test.

    All the notes, dictionaries and translators are forbidden, obviously. This is the time you need to trust yourselves, you need to use the skills you have. Cheating will lead to automatic failure of the test.

    Join Zoom a couple of minutes before your test starts, wait patiently in the waiting room.

    During the test it is okay to ask us to repeat, to speak lower, to say that you don't understand and even pass a question.


    Useful phrases:
    1. Can you repeat? = Voitko toistaa?
    2. Can you speak slower? = Voitko puhua hitaammin?
    3. I don't understand. = En ymmärrä.

    Nähdään pian, see you soon! We'll start 9 am. Check your own time!

    Spoken skills to the MAX
    Starting next week we will start offering extra Spoken skills lessons for you guys. These lessons are offered to you and our another group (Ahmat), so you might meet some new people.
